13/03/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov and Greek counterpart Spilios Spiliotopoulos sealed a framework agreement Friday (11 March) on bilateral military co-operation. 
It outlines the main principles, financial and legal aspects of such collaboration as well as issues related to protecting classified information.
In other news, the Bulgarian Defence Ministry announced on Friday that it has scrapped a deal with Israel's Elbit Systems for modernisation of 12 Soviet-era helicopters. 
The ministry said only that the contract was cancelled due to "failure to reach initially set tender criteria". 
(Bulgarian government Web site, Sega - 11/03/05)
